M; 

Xyleboricus canaliculatus
Eggers, 1923

; 
SD
: Schedl, 1936a-64

Remarks: 84 + 1 (+) spp. Recorded as a polyphyletic genus by Hulcr et al. (2007). Wood and Bright (1992) presented a mixed use of gender as masculine (
capensis
) and neuter.
C. capense
is the correct spelling. Some other specific names are corrected in error to a neuter form that they cannot have, being substantives in apposition (
C. scorpius
) or invariable adjectives (
C. quadricuspis
).

